    ns2:publisher ns2:Little_Brown ;
    ns2:reviewBody """A little red cat leaves the house one day only to encounter an alligator, then a bear. And a chicken, followed by a dragon. The creatures join the cat on his adventures, the chicken lays a surprising egg, and an exhalation of fire forces them to don glasses and so on, through the entire alphabet. Each page features only its capital and lower-case letter; there is no other text, yet the pace, detail, and narrative are rich in discoveries for the reader, and utterly open to interpretation and readings. Many of the scenes use slapstick humour, as when the six characters (egg included) wipe out on a patch of ice, while other scenes are at times nostalgic, with the little red cat dreaming of home.\r
\r
The watercolour and ink illustrations bear the entire narrative weight of this picture book and acquit themselves with seemingly endless range and flair. The book makes use of both dimensions, turning horizontal to show its little posse plummeting off the left page in parachutes. Colourful, cartoonish and charmingly ludicrous, these depictions of the 26 letters manage to raise nuanced insights about friendship and tell a fairly complex quest story.\r
\r
A key at the back of the book lists each letter’s corresponding word.""" ;
