    ns2:publisher ns2:MacMilan ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Here are Little Bo-Peep, Wee Willie Winkie and Little Jack Horner. This illustrated collection of over 60 nursery rhymes includes mostly well-known standards, like “Rock-a-Bye Baby,” “Pat-a-Cake” and “Pease Porridge Hot,” as well as a few less familiar pieces like “Three Wise Men of Gotham,” “Donkey, Donkey, Old and Grey” and “As Tommy Snooks and Betsy Brooks.” Even very short rhymes are featured: “Rain, rain, go away,Come again another day.”\r
The genre itself has long been used to introduce aural and verbal concepts; this book formalizes the educational aspect with concept sections, featuring verbs, colours, specific vocabulary, numbers and letters.\r
Each Mother Goose rhyme is representatively depicted with soft colour spot illustrations that often provide an imaginative leap: Little Jumping Joan is shown riding in a kangaroo pouch; a dragon obligingly breathes fire to warm up the “pease porridge hot.” The images are sweetly old-fashioned, reflecting the age-old status of many of these verses.""" ;
