    ns2:publisher ns2:Annick ;
    ns2:reviewBody """It’s her birthday, and every time Olivia blows out her birthday candles (“Ahhhhhhhhh … Whhhhhhhhhw”) her crazy wishes come true. First she wishes for “snow, snow and more snow,” even though it’s summer. Her parents obligingly bake up a second cake and she wishes for rain, rain and more rain, to wash away the excessive snow. Then sunshine is needed, of course, to dry the flood. That’s when Olivia starts making her own cakes for even more wishes. “‘Olivia,’ said her father, ‘did you wish three words?’ ‘NNNNO.’”\r
Punchy and rhythmic language is rich with repetition and expressive sounds—making for riotous reading aloud. \r
Fun, expressive illustrations in watercolour effects depict hilarious scenes of birthday mayhem. Party-goers skiff through the flooded kitchen in a washtub; a dump truck full of money bounces toward Olivia’s house; shocked parents gaze a Olivia, cradling a rolling pin, as she reveals her final birthday wish. The last image shows the family—now with three new babies—walking down the street in a merry pram-parade.""" ;
