    ns2:publisher "Blue Apple Books"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This specialized ABC book uses both words and pictures to portray a wide variety of dance styles and terms from ballet and break dance to folk dance and tap. The bottom line, according to the dust jacket, is that dance isn’t just an art, “it’s a whole different language.”\r
Each alphabetic entry includes a dance-related term (“Choreographer”), a basic definition (“person who creates the steps to be used in a dance”) and a pronunciation guide. Some entries introduce key vocabulary (improvisation, arabesque, leotard); others connect readers to the dances of diverse cultures (the Hawaiian hula, the Chinese dragon dance).\r
The dynamic layout combines whimsical, expressive collages and playful font. The animated dancers in the bright, colourful drawings have loads of eye-catching appeal.\r
This is a charming introductory resource for young dance enthusiasts and may also inspire readers to consider ABC versions of their own favourite sport or pastime.""" ;
