    ns2:datePublished "2009"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Lee & Low Books"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This picture book biography is a lyrical celebration of Bob Marley’s life and legacy. Its 17 free-verse poems, told in Marley’s voice, capture his conflicted childhood as a bi-racial boy, his father’s absence, his struggles and triumphs, his influences and his dream to “Be the voice of the voiceless.”\r
Taken together, the stand-alone poems also work as a unit to build the narrative arc of the book. In varying degrees, they use repetition, colloquial language and specific lines from Marley’s songs to echo his trademark reggae sound. Strumming his guitar in the lush green setting of the opening spread, he calls himself “the boyFrom Nine Miles . . . The one singLike three little birdsFrom my mum mum belly.”\r
Luminous acrylic paintings in deep, rich hues capture the beautiful landscape of Marley’s Jamaican homeland, the key events and themes in his life, his Rastafarian beliefs, his visionary powers and his love of music. \r
The book includes a brief introductory note about the title, an author’s foreword and four pages of detailed reference notes to accompany the poems, which provide historical context as well as some of the less kid-friendly facts about Marley’s life.""" ;
