    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=54212" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2012"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Quarto"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """What do cats dream about? This picture book offers delightful insights into a house cat’s colourful and adventurous dreams. Sleeping on his comfy, cozy pillow at home, the cat’s dreams leap from deep in the jungle “striped like the shadows, sun-scorched,” “over the bleached plains of Africa” to snowy forests and a river in the tropics. \r
\r
The book’s layout consists of two-page spread vignettes that correspond to the cat’s dreamscape. The watercolour artwork in earthy, rich tones is beautifully detailed and fills entire pages, making this story visually engaging.\r
\r
The text is brief, lyrical but powerfully evocative and lends itself to being read aloud. There are rich opportunities to discuss interesting word choice and geographical locations: “I dream that I walk through resin-scented forest, ears pricked for owl hoot, nose sharp for hare scent, a ghost in the twilight.” \r
\r
The last two pages contain one-paragraph descriptions of the 10 cats, nine big cats and the one domestic cat that are featured in the book. Each description is paired with a realistic illustration. The information presented contains unique facts about each cat, including habitat, personality, nomenclature and what they feed on, providing a fun and educational way to end the book.""" ;
    ns2:title "I Am Cat" ;
