    ns2:publisher "Enchanted Forest"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """From east to west, Canadian provinces and territories are represented in this cute rendering of typical Canadian landscapes. The countrywide sweep mostly follows the progress of a day, beginning at the Atlantic in the morning and hitting Alberta around sunset, with night-time detours in Québec and an aurora borealis in northern Manitoba, until otters in the Vancouver night show that “everywhere babies are going to bed.” \r
The relatively elaborate text mentions the animals and landscapes depicted on each page through figurative language, and conveys more abstract ideas: in the foothills, “the sun is sinking away” while “the leaves whisper autumn tales” around the swampy home of a moose family.\r
Several scenes include people: a Newfoundland and Labrador flag flaps in front of a red clapboard house by the sea as a toddler plays with a Black Lab while his mother hangs laundry on the line; kids wield maple leaves and a boy in a hide jacket and plaid wool hat pulls a sleigh in the illuminated streets of old Québec City; a mother polar bear protects her cubs in the shadow of a tall stone inukshuk. The illustrations themselves are colourful, textured and complex, and mix almost realistic depictions with more cartoonish features.""" ;
