    ns2:datePublished "2018"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Phaidon"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Solid paper-constructions and stylish illustrations make the steps for baking chocolate chip cookies into an interactive story that is a treat to read.\r
Simple instructions illustrate a range of verbs and vocabulary related to baking: “measure the salt,” “scoop the baking soda,” “pour the flour.” Readers may be inspired to write their own recipes for favourite dishes.\r
Graphic-style illustrations use simple forms and colour-blocking to create elegant images that reflect the simplicity of the language. One image shows the pink ring of a mixing bowl, seen from above, as the blue tines of a whisk seem to hover over the swirls of beige-and-brown batter within. Drop-out white text contours around the rim of the bowl: “STEP 2: Mix the brown and white sugars in the large bowl. Add the melted butter and whisk for 1 minute until light and creamy.”\r
Paper-constructed interactive elements allow readers to perform actions as the recipe unfolds: a pull-tab causes a cracked egg to drop into the bowl; a revolving tab causes ingredients to be mixed; yet another allows reader to pull a tray of hot cookies from the oven. In the end, fresh baked cookies, may be lifted off the page and enjoyed: “Taste what you’ve made while they’re still warm. Delicious!”""" ;
