    ns2:reviewBody """Similar in format to the other titles in this series focusing on farm animals, this book introduces children to the anatomy, life cycle and products of goats, as well as to certain breeds (Pygmy, Bagot) and traditions associated with them. It also explores our reasons – dairy products, meat and clothing – for raising them on farms. \r
Suitable for read-aloud audiences or beginning readers, the book conveys easy-to-read facts that are delivered in short blocks of text with a large, kid-friendly font. A bright, appealing table of contents helps readers find information. \r
Lively and engaging, the layout features a variety of eye-catching visuals including coloured photos with labels and captions, such as Farm Facts: “People first kept goats for food and milk more than 9000 years ago.” Words in boldface type help develop vocabulary.\r
The book ends with a simple recipe for a goats’ milk smoothie, a glossary, an index and loads of educational ideas for teachers looking for lessons and activities to accompany or extend the text.""" ;
