    ns2:publisher ns2:Chronicle_Books ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This humorous book outlines 10 steps to story reading, including some preliminary measures such as “find a reading buddy” and “find a cozy reading spot.” We follow a young boy and his reading buddy, a blue dog, through each of the steps as they read a book called The Princess, the Dragon and the Robot.\r
While the story is focused more on the steps than the narrative, readers can create their own narrative based on the illustrations. Step 9 reads: “When you get to the exciting parts, make your voice sound exciting too.” The facing page has some examples to try: ‘“Who dares disturb me in my cave?’ the dragon growled.” The boy’s face in the illustration is animated, with an open mouth and wide eyes while the dog perspires with anticipation.\r
The cartoonish illustrations are done in a pale palette of watercolour. Sometimes the illustrations show the boy and his blue dog in their cozy reading chair. Other times, the illustrations feature those of the book they are reading, with a dragon, a princess and a robot. “If you need to take a break, you can pause for a minute ... and talk to your reading buddy to predict what might happen next.” The facing illustration shows a variety of possibilities, including the princess walking the dragon like a dog and the dragon eating the princess in a sandwich.\r
This fun book brings awareness to the many factors that can make the process of story reading even more fun and enjoyable.""" ;
