    ns2:publisher ns2:Penguin_Random_House ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This rhythmic story stars a young girl whose bedtime routine involves “dancing down the long hall” and “bouncing off the tall wall.” The short, fast-paced rhyming text begs to be read out loud as Lollie dances her way to bed: “Teeth brushing.Music crushing!Bass thumping.Shoulders pumping.”\r
The illustrations, done with watercolour and India ink, are as playful as the text, with swirling colours, approximate lines and exuberant shading that falls well outside the lines. One two-page spread shows Lollie grooving with her dog and cat whose legs are extended in “Body swanking.Hip gyration.” The background is made of multi-coloured swirls that capture their joyful, free movements. Lollie is in her room looking for her pyjamas when her father calls, “It’s fun, hon.But turn the music down some.” Finally in bed, she calls to her parents to say goodnight. She is shown under a comforter made of purple swirls, surrounded by her dog and cat. Her father kisses her goodnight and dims the lights, but sleep is just the beginning for her: “JumpingSnappingNonstop. Lollie’s dreaming hip-hop!” The illustration shows Lollie jiving with her dog and cat in her dreams, wearing her yellow pyjamas and surrounded by multi-coloured swirls. \r
This joyful bedtime routine celebrates movement and music.""" ;
