    ns2:publisher "Flowerpot Press"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Each page features an adorable dog portrait featuring a different breed along with a descriptor ranging from physical to emotional. “Spotted dog” reads the first page, accompanied by a dalmatian puppy gazing innocently into the camera. “Silly dog” reads another, while a golden retriever reclines on its back with its ears splayed on the ground. Not only will readers discover the wide range of different dog breeds, but they will also recognize emotional states that are similar to their own, including shy, playful, curious and happy.\r
The featured breeds range from tiny Pomeranians and dachshunds to big bulldogs and pit bulls. The quality photographs are in full colour. A “dirty dog” is represented by a round white bulldog covered in mud and innocently licking its nose. A corgi dozing, ots head resting on the floor, is a “sleepy dog.” Some photographs occupy two pages while most take up only one with the opposite page rendered in bright blue, red, orange or green. While the text is simple, the photographs inspire discussion and observation about the various qualities each dog exhibits.""" ;
