    ns2:publisher ns2:Orca ;
    ns2:reviewBody """A lawyer appears at high schooler Rennie’s house at a Canadian Forces Base with shocking news. His grandfather has passed away and left Rennie money in his will. But Rennie must fly to Iceland and fulfill his grandfather’s last request.\r
\r
In this fast-paced thriller, Rennie is given a mysterious mission, to return a notebook to the site of a plane crash that happened decades earlier. Put in the care of the family of an old friend of his grandfather’s, Rennie soon finds himself ushered into a maze of multiple mysteries that collide and unfold. Caught in tangled family webs, an unexplained death echoes Rennie’s own secret.\r
\r
Rennie, a teenager grieving his mother’s death, becomes the unwitting detective in an adventure story that has him scaling the waterfalls and glaciers of Iceland’s unique landscape. The first-person narrative is easy to follow and is key to the building suspense. \r
\r
“Every journey starts with the first step. And continues with the next and then the next.” If Rennie thought a trip to the other side of the world would be a way for him to leave behind his stern father and the anger management boot camp he was made to complete, he ultimately learns that wherever you go, you cannot escape who you are: “Secrets come out sooner or later.”""" ;
