ns2:Book998f942b-aab4-4a3c-9cd8-dfa6bf601e6d a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Stacey McAnulty" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=54451" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Penguin_Random_House ;
    ns2:reviewBody """All the fun and excitement of learning a team sport is charmingly and humorously conveyed in this tale that features a quirky player named Max: “I know a lot about soccer. I’ve been playing it for a long time—almost three weeks.”\r
Max’s narrative relates his vision of soccer essentials (“The clouds over the soccer field can be amazing.” “Sometimes there are ladybugs and worms. You should move them so they don’t get hurt.”) Speech-bubble dialogue by Coach, teammates and Max’s mother provide an alternate picture: “Kick the ball, Max!” “Get the ball, Max!” “Max, the ball!”\r
Cute illustrations in colour pencil effects depict a diverse crowd of child-characters in cleats and jerseys, while clever compositions demonstrate soccer as it should be played. The ball’s path, direction and speed are shown in dramatic whoosh-trails across the green turf. One spread shows the impact of a kick-off, while opposing players hip-check to gain control of the ball. Meanwhile, Max is the picture of concentration in the middle of game-play—examining a clover. Other distractions include a dog, the crowd taking his photo and things to do with his hands, “so they don’t get bored.”\r
The interplay between language and images offers tremendous opportunities for discussion—about game rules, techniques and of course, different perspectives. The book’s message of acceptance and individuality is conveyed with flair when Max—“I feel like I’m forgetting something important. Something you have to do in soccer . . . ”—misses an easy goal opportunity. When the referee blows the end-of-game whistle: “SNACK! That’s it. I can’t believe I almost forgot. You get a snack at the end.”""" ;
    ns2:title "Max Explains Everything: Soccer Expert" ;
