    ns2:reviewBody """Simple, brief writing combines with atmospheric charcoal drawings to convey a tale of wait-and-see, as a young boy hopes that an impending storm won’t ruin his beach outing the following day. The language conveys his helpless uncertainty: “every time I look at the sky, it gets darker and darker.…”\r
This quiet tale is carried by the emotional impact of the illustrations. Virtuosic use of charcoal shadows supports the sense of loss over a long anticipated treat. One gorgeous spread shows the boy’s neighbourhood as the storm hits. Erasures make glowing windows and headlights, while expressive scrapings create the dance of glittering rain. Light and dark compete for dominance in successive images, through a dramatic dream sequence of a flying ship and the dawn of a new day. “In the morning, sunshine streams through my window.”\r
The final images introduce a brilliant blue sky and innocuous blue puddles: “Perfect for a day at the beach!”""" ;
