    ns2:publisher ns2:Penguin_Random_House ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Named after trees, sisters Maple and Willow are excited about holiday preparations. But there’s a kink in their festivities when it turns out Maple is allergic to their beloved Christmas tree.\r
Pencil and digitally coloured illustrations present sweet images of the two rosy-cheeked children making the most of winter. The season is shown in its full glory, from the frosty animals that readers can spot across the pages to the image of the family with their tree strapped to the car roof, driving along a country road amid gently falling snow.\r
The dialogue between the girls is funny, believable and a little sassy: “While getting ready for bed, Maple said, ‘Willow, I’m sorry I ruined Christmas.’ ‘I’m sorry you ruined Christmas, too,’ said Willow.” At one point it includes an exchange in pig Latin.\r
Maple’s allergy is a bummer, but using her imagination and resourcefulness, Willow finds just the right way to fix things. Readers may have their own ideas for Christmas tree replacements. This unique Christmas tale can also be used to stimulate discussion about allergies and accommodation.""" ;
