ns2:Bookb8facc7e-e414-48a5-9489-0308b5718c17 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Keith Negley" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=53439" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2015"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Nobrow Press"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Tough guys are like everyone else, as this utterly sweet, good-looking little book explains with very brief language and graphic-style illustrations.\r
Simple forms in contrasting colours are enriched with minimal shading and markings in crayon-style effects. They depict a variety of situations: stress-sweat flies from a masked wrestler before his fight; an astronaut floats in outer space, gripping a family photo. “You might not think it, but tough guys have feelings too.”\r
Readers will appreciate images of loneliness (a superhero sits atop a cityscape, eating his packed lunch), pain (a cowboy tumbles off the rear-end of his horse) and sadness (a knight mourns his broken sword). Short phrases offer insight: “No matter how strong, or fast, or brave they are.”\r
In the end, this fun book’s valuable message is driven home by a cozy bedtime-reading scene between a father and son: “just like these tough guys, who love each other very much.” (As a bonus, spot illustrations on front and back endpapers provide a treasure trove of additional scenes, featuring these two characters.)""" ;
