    ns2:publisher ns2:Penguin_Random_House ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This appetizing and creative counting book promotes both early numeracy and healthy eating. Each number includes the digit (2) and the spelled-out number (two) in a large, boldly coloured font. Each is imaginatively depicted by the appropriate number of vegetable critters, from “one avocado deer” to “ten clementine kitties.” The counting ends with “one big delicious salad” which is followed by a short recipe for dressing.\r
Each number is inventively accompanied by creatures formed by combining a photograph of a vegetable with overlaid ink features transforming the veggie into an animal. Little eyes and a mouth, along with long arms, legs and a tail, turn peppers into monkeys; radishes keep their own tail to become mice; and cucumbers cut into half-circles are extended with tails and toothy jaws into “cucumber alligators.” Even the dressing is playfully metamorphosed, with a salt shaker made into a diving bird, while lemon pigs gaze on.""" ;
