    ns2:datePublished "2015"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Nomad Press"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Each chapter in this overview of five world religions looks at principles, rituals and symbols in each belief system, as well as historical, geographical and demographic information, textual excerpts and corollary information on sites, architecture, food and language. “Facts on Faith” provide secondary details: “Changes in religion,” one notes, “occurred when religious leaders interpreted doctrine in different ways.”\r
Prompts and questions, notably in well-developed “Inquire and Investigate” sections, encourage consideration of the commonalities of these religions, and identify relevant real-life situations, while QR codes link to excerpts of sacred texts.\r
Illustrated panels, peopled with practitioners of the various faiths, provide an accessible visual motif—two women at a multi-faith picnic are portrayed sharing matzo brei and gulab jamun, for instance. A timeline and a glossary allow for a quick reference to religious touchstones and terms.\r
A deeper knowledge of the particularities of various religions can only contribute to better understanding, both of others and of oneself, especially given the belief in the Golden Rule, common to all. As the final chapter reminds us, “every person should treat others as he or she would like to be treated.”""" ;
