    ns2:datePublished "2015"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Little_Brown ;
    ns2:reviewBody """“Roads … go.” “Roads … bend.” “Roads … reach.” Inspiring metaphors advocate for all of life’s explorations: “Roads … merge.Small, distant roads sometimes travel alone,marking the miles out there on their own.Then a new road wants to join in the fun,heads the same way, and the two become one.”\r
An adventurous rabbit bicycles through magical vistas traced in fine pen-line effects and warm colours. The dynamic forms of trees, bulrushes and buildings seem to bend and sway over the winding roads. These detailed, double-page panoramas are rich with stories of their own. An owl hitches a ride in the rabbit’s front basket; a family of mice strap their barge to the rear fender; the lights of a tree-house village glimmer in purple twilight, as the rabbit joins new friends for tea. Through rain and snow, and up tall mountains, these images beautifully reflect the wonder that permeates the language. \r
As the rabbit gazes down on all the landscapes visited, adventure is tempered with reflection: “Where are you going and where you began.What you expected. What you didn’t plan.” Then the road takes this cheerful wanderer back home.""" ;
