ns2:Booke5c7121d-98fb-440b-816e-c14d03f518a8 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Michael Morpurgo" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=54385" ;
    ns2:datePublished "1999"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Egmont"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Michael, his parents and their sheepdog, Stella Artois, set out to sail around the world aboard the Peggy Sue. Michael and Stella are washed overboard during a storm but Michael somehow makes it to a deserted island—or one he imagines to be deserted. Food and water mysteriously appear, saving Michael’s life. After he is stung by jellyfish, he meets Kensuke, who saves him yet again and nurses him back to health. Kensuke, Michael learns, was a doctor in Japan, and was wrecked on the island after Nagasaki. Having lost everything and everyone, he decided to stay. Fiercely protective of his domain and initially of his solitude, Kensuke ultimately wants Michael to stay: “‘You are like son to me now. We happy people. We paint. We fish. We happy. We stay together. You my family now Micasan.’” He changes his mind after imagining Michael’s stricken mother and even considers returning to Japan.\r
With echoes of Robinson Crusoe, this novel is at once a fast-paced adventure story and a calm, subtle meditation on human existence. Kensuke shares survival lessons with his young protégé, such as watching the orangutans to see what could be eaten. The two also articulate important interpersonal lessons about trust and communication, notably when Kensuke feels betrayed by Michael’s attempts to signal the outside world. Michael’s first-person point of view is believably young; Kensuke’s solitude and slight madness are poignant.\r
The opening sections, which include excerpts from Michael’s log, are printed in a different, sans-serif font, as is a later message Michael floats out to his parents in a bottle. Ink drawings punctuate the book: navigational maps of the sail around Australia, for instance, a portrayal of Michael and Stella being overtaken by a wave as the sailboat floats out of reach, and Kensuke leaning over a blanketed Michael, tending to him.""" ;
    ns2:title "Kensuke's Kingdom" ;
