    ns2:datePublished "2010"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Tundra_Books ;
    ns2:reviewBody """“6 seals slipping,” 5 wolves watching,” “4 hares huddling.” Vigorous, minimal language relates this northern countdown, making it a pleasure to read aloud. Muskoxen mingle; ravens rave; caribou crunch. Even the title packs a wallop, with its hint of conservation and a warning about climate change.\r
Painterly illustrations depict realistic portrayals of the animals in typical northern settings, with an attractive, graphic quality in their compositions. White patches on the behinds of 10 caribou flash against the blossoming tundra. Sinuous necks and wing patterns of seven trumpeter swans seem to undulate in a light snowfall.\r
The snowfall grows heavier as the countdown continues. Young readers may need to squint to find “2 snowy owls swooping.” For the finale, a distinctively shaped silhouette rests behind a near-whiteout: 1 moose, silent in the falling snow.” This is a fun, attractive and original little counting book.""" ;
