    ns2:datePublished "2013"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:MacMilan ;
    ns2:reviewBody """At the end of a bumpy school bus ride, a group of young children are keen to go out and play football. Fall leaves tumble as they rake the yard and organize their team. When Sparky the dog runs away with the ball, the inevitable happens – the pile of leaves flies into the air with the collision of the chase. Then it is time to go home. Snow gently falls but there is warm food on the table and football on TV.\r
Thick pages feature children’s round bodies, with spiky hair and tiny noses, that seem to be in perpetual motion, sometimes “floating in the air” – like the whirling drifts of leaves. Illustrations are finely executed in detailed pen and ink with soft watercolour fills for the children’s clothing, rosy cheeks and school bus. Artwork for the grasses and trees resembles etchings in its textural detail.\r
Text is spare and filled with the children’s dialogue and simple description: “Along country lanes, past one fat cow, the school bus rattles.”\r
Pages are tinted with blue as dusk falls and children are called home in this simple, endearing tribute to fall and sporting fun.""" ;
