ns2:Booke8aaecea-ffda-4e8f-959f-08d3a06f7d37 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Julia Finlay Mosca" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=54407" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "The Innovation Press"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This picture book biography about animal science researcher and inventor Dr. Temple Grandin, a person with autism, uses peppy rhymes to convey its messages about being different and exploring our particular gifts and talents. An empathetic perspective outlines Temple’s childhood autistic behaviours (“quite a tantrum she’d throw—KICK HOLLER BANG SHRIEEEEEK! Yet, still, by age three not one word did she speak”) and challenges: “No one really got Temple, but well, then again … the truth of it was, Temple didn’t get THEM.”\r
 \r
Quirky and artful illustrations use simple forms to create fun, diagrammatic images that depict key moments in Temple’s life and her unique thought processes. One image shows Temple clasping wooden boards, as dotted lines form a triangle, connecting her mind with two thoughts: a cow in a squeeze chute, ready for inoculation, and herself, lifting the door from a similarly constructed wood box. (“So, she built a machine like she’d seen on some farms, an INVENTION that hugged her with boards, and not arms.”) A double-page spread shows her standing before her design of a curving cattle chute, as happy cows munch grass in the distance. In the foreground, farmers’ hands consult a guide to “Livestock Handling and Transport by T. Grandin.”\r
 \r
The final spread shows Temple in her trademark cowboy-garb, as planes travel dotted routes on a map of the world, symbolizing the scientist’s renown for her discoveries in animal science and autism. Each person is special—so UNIQUE in our minds. This world needs YOUR ideas. It takes brains of ALL kinds!’”\r
 \r
An abundance of back material includes a timeline, additional biographical information and a letter to readers by Dr. Grandin herself.""" ;
    ns2:title "Girl Who Thought in Pictures: the Story of Dr. Temple Grandin" ;
